HEADWORD: Uncentury
<hw>Un*cen"tu*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>century</ets>.]</ety> <def>To remove from its
actual century.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It has first to <qex>uncentury</qex> itself.</q> <rj><qau>H.
Drummond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncertain</ent>⟦br⟧
